.START 

Japan posted an unadjusted trade surplus of $3.27 billion for the second 10 days of September, falling from $4.14 billion a year earlier, the Finance Ministry announced. 

The figure compared with an unadjusted surplus of $2.53 billion for the first 10 days of the month, which was higher than $2.41 billion recorded a year earlier. 

Exports for the second 10 days of September rose 2.1% to $14.15 billion from $13.86 billion a year earlier.
Imports surged 12% to $10.88 billion from $9.72 billion. 

